                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .project-details__intro-text-wrapper
                            .project-details__introduction
                                %p A collection of social media work spanning four distinct clients: Sharelov, a SaaS social media management platform; Island Finance, a personal loan company; Chat, an advertising agency; and Ed Harvest, an emerging music artist. Despite the variety, each project started in the same place: establishing a consistent brand aesthetic and voice, then building a content approach around the specific audience and goals of that client.
                                %br
                                %p The range of voices across the four reflects how differently social media has to work depending on context. Ed Harvest's account was crafted to feel personal and unfiltered, as if he were posting himself. Chat and Sharelov land in a middle ground, friendly and approachable but positioned as knowledgeable. Island Finance takes a more direct tone, prioritizing clarity and trust. The grid aesthetics follow the same logic, each visually distinct to match what the brand needed to communicate at a glance.
