            .project-details__company-wrapper.gallery__company4
                .columns
                    .column.is-4
                        %h2 Ed Harvest
                        .project-details__scope-wrapper
                            %h3 Project Scope
                            %ul
                                %li Art Direction
                                %li Graphic Design
                                %li Social media strategy and content planning
                                %li Post ideation
                                %li Mood boarding for photo and video shoots
                                %li Storyboarding for short form videos
                                %li Photo editing and AI-assisted image creation
                                %li Asset selection and grid curation
                                %li Video editing for reels, lyrics videos, and promotional clips
                                %li Guerrilla marketing and PR box campaign coordination
                    .column.is-8
                        .project-details__description-wrapper
                            %p Social media for Ed Harvest, a Puerto Rican singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist making his mark in the Spanish rock scene.
                            %p 
                                %strong Challenge:
                                How do you build a serious artist brand for someone who is just getting started, without making them look like they are just getting started?
                            %h4 Key Takeaways
                            %ul
                                %li.c4 
                                    %strong Ditching the Influencer Aesthetic:
                                    Ed's feed needed a full reset. We stripped back the text-heavy, influencer-style posts and rebuilt around a cleaner, photography-focused grid that let the music and his image speak for themselves.
                                %li.c4 
                                    %strong Leaning Into Lyrics:
                                    Lyrics videos featuring the hook of each single became a core content format, giving listeners something to latch onto and making the songs recognizable before they even hit play.
                                %li.c4 
                                    %strong Relatable Over Promotional:
                                    Meme-style and POV reels framed around his music encouraged reposts and helped new listeners connect with the songs on a personal level.
                                %li.c4 
                                    %strong Photodump Carousels:
                                    Thematic carousels tied to each single gave the feed a cohesive, intentional feel while creating a natural way to resurface music without it feeling repetitive.
                                %li.c4 
                                    %strong Going Guerrilla:
                                    The campaign extended beyond social with playlist outreach, physical posters placed around the city, and a PR box campaign built around a fake breakup company called Centro Adiós that redirected to his music.
                            %br
                            %p 
                                %strong The Results:
                                230 new Instagram followers in a month, 30k+ streams in a single week, 4k website visits with presaves in 24 hours, and a top 2 spot on an AZ rock radio station within a week of release.
                                

